<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<LanguageData>
  
  <!-- EN: metapod -->
  <VRE_MetapodHediff.label>化形茧</VRE_MetapodHediff.label>
  <!-- EN: A large cocoon formed by an insector undergoing a metamorphosis. If destroyed, the insector inside will die. After metamorphosis is complete, the insector will emerge from their metapod with a brand new genetic composition. -->
  <VRE_MetapodHediff.description>异虫种为进行变态发育而构造的大型茧。如果将其摧毁，处于内部的异虫种也会随之死亡。当变态发育完成后，异虫种会破茧而出，并形成全新的基因种系。</VRE_MetapodHediff.description>
  
  <!-- EN: Metapod sickness -->
  <VRE_MetapodSickness.label>化形茧后遗症</VRE_MetapodSickness.label>
  <!-- EN: After-effects of undergoing an evolution via a metapod. The insectoid metapod replaces and mutates the genome of the individual. Upon exiting the metapod, the body takes time to restart and rebalance its natural metabolic processes. Duration of the metapod sickness depends on the duration spent in the metapod. -->
  <VRE_MetapodSickness.description>通过变态发育形成全新基因种系所产生的后遗症，身体需要一定的时间来恢复生理机能和平衡新陈代谢过程。在化形茧内部待的越久，后遗症的持续时间也就越长。不会造成长期伤害。</VRE_MetapodSickness.description>
  
</LanguageData>